ortion of self-reported cigarette counts.\nHigher nicotine dependence, white ethnicity and male sex are associated with\ngreater remembered smoking given the EMA count. The model is potentially useful\nin other applications where it is desirable to understand the process by which\nsubjects remember and report true observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Jan 2013 09:26:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-01-14"}
